<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="265" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="4.[1386,2597,289,683]" pageId="4" pageNumber="265">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1389,1754,407,440]" pageId="4" pageNumber="265">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
CITES Appendix II. Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List. The Sumatran Treeshrew was recently elevated from subspecific status, and new research is needed to fully understand its conservation status. Within the distribution of the Sumatran Treeshrew, there has been substantial conversion of native forests for agricultural purposes, which no doubt represents a significant conservation threat.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
